01:33:00,705 --> 01:33:04,398
<i>Some sort of a yampy bloody corporate test
or something, I don't know but...</i>

1265
01:33:04,398 --> 01:33:06,627
Take a rest whenever you get a chance.

1266
01:33:06,627 --> 01:33:08,129
<i>Sorry, my love. What you were saying?</i>

1267
01:33:08,129 --> 01:33:09,631
You've only got a few hours.

1268
01:33:09,632 --> 01:33:13,410
I can't hear you very well.
I'm sorry, I can't hear ya. Wish me luck.

1269
01:33:13,559 --> 01:33:15,569
- Good luck.
- I love you, darling.

1270
01:33:15,995 --> 01:33:18,180
<i>After 23 hours here at Daytona,</i>

1271
01:33:18,180 --> 01:33:20,641
<i>Walt Hansgen,
driving a green and white Ford</i>

1272
01:33:20,641 --> 01:33:25,175
<i>has a commanding lead
over Ken Miles and Shelby American.</i>

1273
01:33:27,635 --> 01:33:31,134
We're locked out, ain't nothing
Miles can do this late in the race.

1274
01:33:32,210 --> 01:33:34,975
Engine's hot,
we gotta keep it under 6 thou'.

1275
01:34:22,528 --> 01:34:24,492
Alright.

1276
01:34:49,202 --> 01:34:50,963
She could come apart.

1277
01:34:51,119 --> 01:34:52,693
One way to find out.

1278
01:34:55,632 --> 01:34:58,341
I thought we were keeping
him under 6000.

1279
01:34:58,341 --> 01:34:59,898
Shut up, Don.

1280
01:35:09,452 --> 01:35:11,725
<i>We've only minutes of racing
left here at Daytona,</i>

1281
01:35:11,726 --> 01:35:13,879
<i>a pitched battle for the
lead is being raised</i>

1282
01:35:13,879 --> 01:35:16,885
<i>as the #98 Ford makes an
incredible late surge.</i>

1283
01:35:16,886 --> 01:35:19,497
- What's happening?
- He's moving up.

1284
01:35:19,949 --> 01:35:22,496
<i>Ken Miles' desperate bid for the win...</i>

1285
01:35:32,215 --> 01:35:34,400
White flag, last lap!

1286
01:35:39,663 --> 01:35:41,999
Miles is pushing him, hard.

1287
01:35:52,443 --> 01:35:53,902
That's it.

1288
01:36:04,679 --> 01:36:07,887
<i>Ken Miles drafts Walt Hansgen
coming in to the final turn.</i>

1289
01:36:34,502 --> 01:36:35,776
Come on, come on!

1290
01:36:39,469 --> 01:36:41,047
What the hell?

1291
01:36:48,849 --> 01:36:50,022
Come on!

1292
01:36:50,699 --> 01:36:52,518
Alright.

1293
01:36:56,239 --> 01:36:58,070
Look at this now.

1294
01:37:02,795 --> 01:37:03,938
Damn it!

1295
01:37:20,799 --> 01:37:22,469
How about that?

1296
01:37:33,813 --> 01:37:34,719
Yes, Leo?

1297
01:37:34,720 --> 01:37:37,232
Mr. Ford, sir. We won.

1298
01:37:38,855 --> 01:37:41,205
We won. Ford won Daytona.

1299
01:37:42,987 --> 01:37:45,145
And which team was it, Leo?

1300
01:37:46,015 --> 01:37:48,968
Shelby American, Miles driving.

1301
01:37:50,417 --> 01:37:52,121
Son of a bitch.

1302
01:37:54,258 --> 01:37:57,618
Where the hell is he?
Hang on, wait a minute.

1303
01:37:57,986 --> 01:38:00,707
Someone lost a bulldog on the beach!

1304
01:38:01,493 --> 01:38:03,769
No, no. Come on, Come on.

1305
01:38:07,482 --> 01:38:09,436
Someone get this man a drink.

1306
01:38:25,835 --> 01:38:26,835
Oi!

1307
01:38:28,136 --> 01:38:30,538
In bed you!
What are you doing?

1308
01:38:30,919 --> 01:38:32,705
Dirty stop out.

1309
01:38:33,136 --> 01:38:38,040
I was drawing a map,
so I could follow you at Le Mans.

1310
01:38:42,155 --> 01:38:43,706
Look at that.

1311
01:38:44,640 --> 01:38:46,339
That is spot on.

1312
01:38:46,869 --> 01:38:48,971
You are a dab hand,
very accurate.

1313
01:38:50,407 --> 01:38:53,607
- Tell me about the track.
- No, I can't, Petey.

1314
01:38:54,158 --> 01:38:55,799
Please.

1315
01:39:03,989 --> 01:39:06,180
We start at the start line.

1316
01:39:06,894 --> 01:39:10,469
You actually start here, because you
have to run to your car at Le Mans.

1317
01:39:10,470 --> 01:39:11,740
True enough.

1318
01:39:12,647 --> 01:39:16,912
Once your old man
manages to hobble over and pull out.

1319
01:39:17,218 --> 01:39:19,475
- And not hit anyone.
- Yes, right.

1320
01:39:21,151 --> 01:39:25,209
Accelerate, very hard up to Dunlop bridge.

1321
01:39:25,664 --> 01:39:30,113
Road banking away from you.
Then down through the trees to the Esses.

1322
01:39:30,436 --> 01:39:35,025
Accelerate up to Terte Rouge,
critical first gear corner.

1323
01:39:35,444 --> 01:39:42,194
Fast entry, keep your speed up
for your exit onto Mulsanne.

1324
01:39:42,564 --> 01:39:46,529
Long straight-away,
hemmed in by poplars, Top gear.

1325
01:39:46,985 --> 01:39:52,996
210 mph, then down to third,
revs up, revs are your friend.

1326
01:39:53,555 --> 01:39:59,069
Get a maximum exit,
Let the car run free, Over the brow

1327
01:39:59,358 --> 01:40:05,963
then wham, the Mulsanne Corner,
Accelerate to Arnage.

1328
01:40:06,232 --> 01:40:09,906
Over the rise to the White House.
You get that right and

1329
01:40:12,837 --> 01:40:18,007
your first 3.5 minutes of the 24 hours.

1330
01:40:18,930 --> 01:40:19,930
But...

1331
01:40:19,931 --> 01:40:24,940
You can't make every lap perfect.

1332
01:40:26,117 --> 01:40:28,193
But I can try.

1333
01:40:33,426 --> 01:40:36,751
Alright, off to bed you.

1334
01:40:39,916 --> 01:40:45,378
I will wake you before
I leave for France.

1335
01:40:45,612 --> 01:40:47,156
I promise.

1336
01:40:47,329 --> 01:40:49,826
Okay, goodnight.

1337
01:41:19,781 --> 01:41:22,196
Where is that? Hotel Champier?

1338
01:41:24,041 --> 01:41:25,402
Where?

1339
01:42:11,530 --> 01:42:13,706
It's gonna rain again tomorrow.

1340
01:42:18,756 --> 01:42:20,577
There's always rain here.

1341
01:42:23,429 --> 01:42:25,426
Start will be dry, though.

1342
01:42:26,582 --> 01:42:28,890
We'll swap out your tires come rain.

1343
01:42:31,229 --> 01:42:32,781
Yeah.

1344
01:42:35,701 --> 01:42:39,483
Might be smart to sleep, bulldog.

1345
01:42:41,312 --> 01:42:42,873
You too.

1346
01:42:43,668 --> 01:42:45,510
I'm not driving.

1347
01:42:47,989 --> 01:42:50,866
That's a bloody shame, that.

1348
01:42:51,234 --> 01:42:53,645
Oh hell, I couldn't make this team.

1349
01:42:58,272 --> 01:43:00,473
I'm gonna walk the first corner.

1350
01:43:02,090 --> 01:43:03,839
Now I figured.

1351
01:43:14,332 --> 01:43:16,147
Counting on it.

1352
01:43:50,007 --> 01:43:51,289
Hey, Ken.

1353
01:43:51,461 --> 01:43:52,908
Chaz.

1354
01:44:07,119 --> 01:44:11,346
<i>If this were a beauty pageant,
we just lost.</i>

1355
01:44:12,503 --> 01:44:13,966
Looks fast, doesn't it?

1356
01:44:14,415 --> 01:44:16,379
Looks aren't everything.

1357
01:44:20,374 --> 01:44:23,431
Scarfiotti and Bandini
start for Ferrari.

1358
01:44:29,117 --> 01:44:30,150
You can take him.

1359
01:44:30,151 --> 01:44:32,470
<i>4 minutes, Ken.
4 minutes, buddy.</i>

1360
01:44:32,649 --> 01:44:35,617
<i>- Live from Le Mans, France.</i>
- Mom! Come on!

1361
01:44:36,159 --> 01:44:38,106
Alright, I'm coming.

1362
01:44:38,418 --> 01:44:40,766
<i>The 24 Hours of Le Mans.</i>

1363
01:44:46,066 --> 01:44:48,470
<i>Drivers, please take your places.</i>

1364
01:45:07,013 --> 01:45:10,156
- There he is.
<i>- And here they are lined up, ready to go.</i>

1365
01:46:03,514 --> 01:46:04,959
Bloody joking!

1366
01:46:14,092 --> 01:46:15,432
It's all right, son.

1367
01:46:18,178 --> 01:46:20,148
You looked great out there, sir.

1368
01:46:20,798 --> 01:46:22,374
What happened to Miles?

1369
01:46:30,988 --> 01:46:32,757
Bloody hell!

1370
01:46:43,316 --> 01:46:44,531
Poxy bastard!

1371
01:47:20,254 --> 01:47:23,911
<i>After one lap, Bandini,
Ferrari is in first place.</i>

1372
01:47:27,990 --> 01:47:29,634
Where's Miles?

1373
01:47:31,641 --> 01:47:33,862
- Where the hell is Ken?
- I don't know.

1374
01:47:42,947 --> 01:47:45,501
He's coming in.

1375
01:47:45,502 --> 01:47:48,151
Let's go! Faster! Come on!
Let's Go! Move it!

1376
01:47:48,491 --> 01:47:50,194
I think it's his door.

1377
01:47:50,195 --> 01:47:52,364
<i>That's a rough start for the Ford team.</i>

1378
01:47:55,860 --> 01:47:58,929
The bloody door won't close!

1379
01:47:58,930 --> 01:48:01,197
- Alright, alright.
<i>- Maybe it's the heat.</i>

1380
01:48:04,196 --> 01:48:05,052
Try that.

1381
01:48:05,053 --> 01:48:07,261
Shelby! What the hell is wrong?

1382
01:48:08,138 --> 01:48:11,178
<i>- Something's hitting the frame.</i>
- Oh, you're joking, aren't you?

1383
01:48:11,561 --> 01:48:13,200
Guys, get out of the way!

1384
01:48:13,346 --> 01:48:15,043
Get out of the way! Hold.

1385
01:48:16,323 --> 01:48:17,962
Go, go, go!

1386
01:48:26,210 --> 01:48:28,182
He's back out, go!

1387
01:48:55,199 --> 01:48:57,777
<i>Tremendous gains for Ken Miles and Ford...</i>

1388
01:48:57,778 --> 01:49:00,520
Come on dad, come on.

1389
01:49:08,752 --> 01:49:11,455
<i>Ken Miles, Ford, has set a new lap record,</i>

1390
01:49:11,455 --> 01:49:13,618
<i>3 minutes and 34 seconds.</i>

1391
01:49:29,563 --> 01:49:33,742
Shelby, he's pushing the car too hard.
That's not the plan.

1392
01:49:34,626 --> 01:49:36,190
Plan's changed.

1393
01:50:03,560 --> 01:50:06,873
Lap is 3.34, track is 8.36.

1394
01:50:06,873 --> 01:50:09,219
Someone tell me the mph!

1395
01:50:18,033 --> 01:50:20,130
<i>3:31.9 that's a...</i>

1396
01:50:20,131 --> 01:50:21,786
Another lap record.

1397
01:50:27,377 --> 01:50:29,021
Let's go, let's go, boys!

1398
01:50:29,565 --> 01:50:32,323
- Tea's ready, Ken.
- Thank you, Chaz.

1399
01:50:32,726 --> 01:50:35,873
- Happy Birthday, old chap.
- Cheers, mate. Great run.

1400
01:50:44,976 --> 01:50:46,776
You're 3 seconds
faster than Gurney.

1401
01:50:46,892 --> 01:50:49,329
If you hadn't blown the
start you'd be in the lead.

1402
01:50:49,413 --> 01:50:52,123
- Can you keep this up?
- Can the car?

1403
01:50:54,527 --> 01:50:59,487
<i>There has been an incident on turn 6.
#18 and #26 have collided.</i>

1404
01:51:24,643 --> 01:51:27,915
<i>It appears, Ferrari, #20,
Ludovico Scarfiotti</i>

1405
01:51:27,916 --> 01:51:29,916
<i>has also left the track.</i>

1406
01:51:39,079 --> 01:51:41,907
- All right, watch your head.
- Thank you.

1407
01:51:42,156 --> 01:51:44,162
Have a good dinner, sir.

1408
01:51:44,729 --> 01:51:46,623
Oi, McLaren's pitting.

1409
01:51:50,202 --> 01:51:52,501
Mr. Ford's probably going
somewhere nice for dinner.

1410
01:51:52,502 --> 01:51:54,414
What do you mean 'probably'?

1411
01:51:54,415 --> 01:51:55,739
Rain's coming.

1412
01:51:55,909 --> 01:51:57,160
Alright.

1413
01:52:12,887 --> 01:52:14,392
Coming in.

1414
01:52:22,825 --> 01:52:24,989
- Engine's running hot, Pops.
- Alright.

1415
01:52:25,152 --> 01:52:26,681
She's hot, mate. Crack on.

1416
01:52:29,691 --> 01:52:30,998
Tire.

1417
01:52:37,680 --> 01:52:40,529
- We're at 220. We're okay.
- Alright.

1418
01:52:44,739 --> 01:52:46,644
- Let's go.
- Swap that out.

1419
01:52:57,635 --> 01:52:58,990
Go! Go!

1420
01:53:06,453 --> 01:53:08,035
Hey, I need a stopwatch.

1421
01:53:37,930 --> 01:53:42,285
<i>Lorenzo Bandini remains
in first place for Ferrari.</i>

1422
01:53:56,806 --> 01:53:58,852
Easy, Dan. You're getting boxed in.

1423
01:53:58,853 --> 01:54:00,877
He's not batting
on a full wicket, that one.

1424
01:54:06,750 --> 01:54:08,493
Easy, Dan.

1425
01:54:09,912 --> 01:54:11,514
Oh bloody hell!

1426
01:54:12,756 --> 01:54:14,797
You arsehole!

1427
01:54:31,198 --> 01:54:33,298
Oh, piss off!

1428
01:54:35,731 --> 01:54:37,274
You wanker!

1429
01:54:44,286 --> 01:54:47,078
Face like a sprat arse, don't ya?

1430
01:55:00,537 --> 01:55:04,766
<i>Porsche #58 with an unidentified Ford
are run off the track,</i>

1431
01:55:04,767 --> 01:55:05,767
<i>at Arnarge.</i>

1432
01:55:16,672 --> 01:55:18,455
Nice stopwatch.

1433
01:55:18,835 --> 01:55:20,925
You want one? They're Italian.

1434
01:55:43,782 --> 01:55:47,222
<i>Ken Miles in Ford #1,
and Bandini in Ferrari 21</i>

1435
01:55:47,222 --> 01:55:48,776
<i>are locked in a battle
against the elements</i>

1436
01:55:48,777 --> 01:55:50,778
<i>as they push their cars to the limit.</i>

1437
01:55:50,779 --> 01:55:52,677
<i>Past the White House corner.</i>

1438
01:56:00,941 --> 01:56:03,944
Yes, sir? Yes, sir.

1439
01:56:06,737 --> 01:56:08,425
Okay, sir. Right away, sir.

1440
01:56:15,217 --> 01:56:16,485
Hey!

1441
01:56:18,707 --> 01:56:20,161
Give me that.

1442
01:56:22,310 --> 01:56:23,617
Dumbass.

1443
01:56:23,618 --> 01:56:25,120
Mr. Shelby.

1444
01:57:07,430 --> 01:57:09,011
Here we go.

1445
01:57:12,322 --> 01:57:14,425
Come on, girl. Come on.

1446
01:57:20,405 --> 01:57:22,441
Hold it together now.

1447
01:57:40,795 --> 01:57:41,650
Come on!

1448
01:57:41,656 --> 01:57:46,697
<i>Leader at this moment is Ferrari #21,
being driven by Lorenzo Bandini.</i>

1449
01:57:46,698 --> 01:57:49,310
His brakes are shot.
Alright, here we go.

1450
01:57:49,429 --> 01:57:53,950
<i>It looks like Ken Miles is bringing
the #1 Ford into the pits very slowly.</i>

1451
01:57:57,478 --> 01:58:00,114
Brakes! Nothing! Gone!

1452
01:58:00,418 --> 01:58:02,323
Alright. Let's go, let's go, let's go!

1453
01:58:03,912 --> 01:58:06,683
I had him, I almost had him!

1454
01:58:08,528 --> 01:58:10,951
Well, he's putting another
lap on us now.

1455
01:58:14,753 --> 01:58:16,500
Now, now! Faster!

1456
01:58:20,634 --> 01:58:22,634
