01:59:01,498 --> 01:59:03,767
where I can't swap out
my upright assembly.

1466
01:59:03,767 --> 01:59:04,893
A part is a part.

1467
01:59:04,893 --> 01:59:06,972
Be it a brake caliper or a rotor
or an upright assembly

1468
01:59:06,973 --> 01:59:08,978
and I can swap out
any damn thing I want to.

1469
01:59:10,137 --> 01:59:11,897
We read your damn rule book.

1470
01:59:17,712 --> 01:59:20,044
Bandini's pitting, He's pitting!

1471
01:59:27,361 --> 01:59:29,919
Oh, what a shame. I think he blew a line.

1472
01:59:29,919 --> 01:59:32,249
Well, he was trying to
keep up with you.

1473
01:59:41,748 --> 01:59:44,101
I don't speak Italian,
but he ain't happy.

1474
01:59:55,366 --> 01:59:57,946
Get me out of here, Pops.
Come on!

1475
01:59:58,978 --> 02:00:00,511
Almost set, Ken.

1476
02:00:04,133 --> 02:00:05,537
All yours, Ken.

1477
02:00:05,537 --> 02:00:08,320
Alright listen, you can still take
him, but you gotta pass him twice.

1478
02:00:08,321 --> 02:00:10,455
I get it, pass him twice.

1479
02:00:17,395 --> 02:00:22,790
<i>Ford #1, driven by Ken Miles is back out.
Hot on the heels of Bandini in Ferrari 21.</i>

1480
02:01:20,705 --> 02:01:23,810
Not bloody good enough Miles!
Come on!

1481
02:01:24,447 --> 02:01:26,243
He's off his pace.

1482
02:01:27,468 --> 02:01:29,505
He doesn't trust the car yet.

1483
02:01:29,907 --> 02:01:32,784
Come on, Ken.
I gave you new brakes, buddy.

1484
02:01:38,772 --> 02:01:40,321
Alright,

1485
02:01:41,615 --> 02:01:43,410
what did you come here for?

1486
02:01:45,762 --> 02:01:47,589
Let's do it.

1487
02:02:11,522 --> 02:02:13,390
That's it, come on!

1488
02:02:24,498 --> 02:02:26,221
He ain't done it yet.

1489
02:02:29,647 --> 02:02:31,308
He needs to take another lap on him.

1490
02:02:55,322 --> 02:02:59,351
- He needs to pit soon.
- He needs to catch Bandini first.

1491
02:03:09,809 --> 02:03:11,414
All right, you bastard.

1492
02:03:12,590 --> 02:03:14,186
Let's do this again.

1493
02:03:43,578 --> 02:03:44,741
Come on, girl.

1494
02:03:45,284 --> 02:03:47,845
That's my girl, that's my girl!

1495
02:04:07,486 --> 02:04:10,232
Oh my God, Oh my God!

1496
02:04:10,755 --> 02:04:12,499
Bloody hell!

1497
02:04:25,955 --> 02:04:28,280
He did it. We're in the lead.

1498
02:04:28,605 --> 02:04:29,978
Are we in the lead?

1499
02:04:30,092 --> 02:04:31,825
What about Bandini?

1500
02:04:32,560 --> 02:04:34,173
Where's Bandini?

1501
02:04:34,576 --> 02:04:38,126
He's done, finished. Ferrari's over.

1502
02:04:38,127 --> 02:04:40,254
McLaren's 4 minutes behind him in a GT.

1503
02:04:40,255 --> 02:04:44,146
So we're laying Ken first,
and 2 and 3. All Fords.

1504
02:05:05,961 --> 02:05:07,686
The Deuce is coming.

1505
02:05:16,361 --> 02:05:19,371
Ken's up in a half an hour.
Want me to wake him?

1506
02:05:19,372 --> 02:05:21,136
No, let him sleep.

1507
02:05:22,448 --> 02:05:24,285
- Unbelievable.
- Thank you.

1508
02:05:24,569 --> 02:05:26,524
- Good job.
- Not quite there yet, but...

1509
02:05:27,893 --> 02:05:29,570
There he is.

1510
02:05:31,430 --> 02:05:33,115
Brief me, Leo.

1511
02:05:33,385 --> 02:05:35,736
We're running one, two, three, Mr. Ford.

1512
02:05:36,602 --> 02:05:39,032
- Who's in the lead?
- Him. Miles.

1513
02:05:41,877 --> 02:05:43,937
I was thinking, Mr. Ford.

1514
02:05:44,364 --> 02:05:47,458
Wouldn't it be great
if all three Fords lined up

1515
02:05:47,459 --> 02:05:50,498
across the finish line at
the exact same time?

1516
02:05:50,688 --> 02:05:52,768
They'll lined up and came home together.

1517
02:05:52,769 --> 02:05:55,439
Ford, Ford, Ford.

1518
02:05:55,896 --> 02:05:57,982
I don't think we can actually do that, sir.

1519
02:05:59,181 --> 02:06:00,594
Why not?

1520
02:06:01,277 --> 02:06:06,316
Miles is laps ahead, Leo.
What would you have him do, slow down?

1521
02:06:07,815 --> 02:06:09,375
Yeah.

1522
02:06:20,971 --> 02:06:22,892
He thinks it'll be
a historic moment for Ford,

1523
02:06:22,893 --> 02:06:24,464
it'll make a great photograph.

1524
02:06:26,279 --> 02:06:28,782
Shelby, Miles needs to be
a team player here.

1525
02:06:29,113 --> 02:06:30,282
And so do you.

1526
02:06:30,400 --> 02:06:32,276
Are you gonna tell him or
you need me to?

1527
02:06:33,832 --> 02:06:36,321
Don't go near my driver. Go on.

1528
02:06:37,291 --> 02:06:39,873
- This is what Mr. Ford wants.
- Go on now.

1529
02:06:40,495 --> 02:06:42,535
- He expects loyalty.
- Go on.

1530
02:06:59,412 --> 02:07:03,008
Guys, let's go. 
Come on, let's go.

1531
02:07:06,911 --> 02:07:08,289
What'd Beebe want?

1532
02:07:14,244 --> 02:07:15,924
It's off the scale, isn't it?

1533
02:07:21,357 --> 02:07:23,491
They want you to slow down.

1534
02:07:27,259 --> 02:07:29,135
Run that by me again.

1535
02:07:29,384 --> 02:07:31,369
They want you to slow down.

1536
02:07:33,864 --> 02:07:36,952
You're outshining their car, Ken.
You're 4 minutes up on McLaren.

1537
02:07:36,953 --> 02:07:38,277
The Deuce wants the three Fords

1538
02:07:38,278 --> 02:07:40,893
across the finish line:
one, two, three, all together.

1539
02:07:46,598 --> 02:07:49,576
They're asking that you
be a team player.

1540
02:07:50,359 --> 02:07:52,231
And make that photograph
happen for 'em.

1541
02:07:52,232 --> 02:07:55,921
A photograph, that's good.

1542
02:07:55,922 --> 02:07:58,422
That is good!

1543
02:08:00,561 --> 02:08:05,548
Ken, even if you tie for first,
you'd still be first man ever to win

1544
02:08:05,779 --> 02:08:08,708
Sebring, Daytona, Le Mans
in the same year.

1545
02:08:09,198 --> 02:08:11,311
You'll have a triple crown.

1546
02:08:17,695 --> 02:08:19,495
Look, I didn't get...

1547
02:08:20,896 --> 02:08:23,816
I haven't been able to get you
to follow an order since day one.

1548
02:08:24,174 --> 02:08:26,539
Whatever you wanna do
is fine with me.

1549
02:08:27,872 --> 02:08:29,659
My choice?

1550
02:08:30,747 --> 02:08:32,509
Your choice.

1551
02:08:38,694 --> 02:08:42,349
Engine's running at boiling.
The brakes are shot.

1552
02:08:45,418 --> 02:08:46,907
How was that?

1553
02:08:48,245 --> 02:08:49,314
Taken care of.

1554
02:08:49,499 --> 02:08:53,007
The car is yours, Ken.
Ken, the car is yours.

1555
02:08:54,632 --> 02:08:56,655
Car is yours, Ken.

1556
02:09:29,485 --> 02:09:33,033
<i>It's the Fords that are the cars
to beat, claiming the top 3 positions.</i>

1557
02:09:33,034 --> 02:09:34,810
What the hell is he doing?

1558
02:09:39,709 --> 02:09:42,397
Don't answer that!
Get away from it!

1559
02:09:42,546 --> 02:09:44,160
Get away from it!

1560
02:10:10,842 --> 02:10:13,564
- He's gonna break his own record.
- Shut up!

1561
02:10:22,526 --> 02:10:24,170
Wait for it.

1562
02:10:25,791 --> 02:10:27,228
Wait for it.

1563
02:10:30,226 --> 02:10:31,350
Now.

1564
02:10:37,113 --> 02:10:39,685
Miles!

1565
02:11:15,056 --> 02:11:16,813
Bellissimo.

1566
02:11:16,935 --> 02:11:20,449
3:30.6.
That's another record.

1567
02:11:26,116 --> 02:11:28,335
That's a perfect lap.

1568
02:11:28,336 --> 02:11:30,218
<i>And virtually guaranteeing 1st place</i>

1569
02:11:30,219 --> 02:11:33,695
<i>for Shelby American and
their exciting GT-40</i>

1570
02:11:33,828 --> 02:11:41,046
<i>Ken Miles and Shelby American's Ford #1
just beat his own lap record, 3:30.6.</i>

1571
02:11:41,047 --> 02:11:44,039
Bring him in, right now!
He's outta control!

1572
02:11:44,487 --> 02:11:47,570
Bring him in before he wrecks that car
and we don't finish!

1573
02:11:49,765 --> 02:11:51,121
Bring him in, Shelby!

1574
02:11:51,274 --> 02:11:54,438
Or I will get you banned
from the SCCA and the FIA.

1575
02:11:55,898 --> 02:12:00,112
Ken Miles is behind the wheel, Leo.
That's his car to the finish.

1576
02:12:01,652 --> 02:12:10,413
<i>H-a-p-p-y, I'm h-a-p-p-y,
I know I am, I'm sure I am...</i>

1577
02:13:35,184 --> 02:13:37,425
Come on, lads. Where are ya?

1578
02:13:48,122 --> 02:13:49,779
What's he doing?

1579
02:13:50,358 --> 02:13:52,669
Mom, why is he slowing down?

1580
02:14:24,295 --> 02:14:26,735
The three Fords are going to
cross the line together.

1581
02:14:26,999 --> 02:14:29,167
Ken Miles slowed down.
He waited for them.

1582
02:14:29,401 --> 02:14:31,927
Dad? No.

1583
02:14:32,062 --> 02:14:32,994
- It's Alright.
- Dad.

1584
02:14:32,995 --> 02:14:35,394
It's Alright. He's bringing them in.

1585
02:14:35,395 --> 02:14:36,455
<i>...lead by Ken Miles...</i>

1586
02:14:36,456 --> 02:14:39,616
<i>- He's bringing them all in together.
- He's certainly the leader of this group.</i>

1587
02:14:40,375 --> 02:14:42,014
Good for you.

1588
02:14:42,647 --> 02:14:44,382
Good for you, Ken.

1589
02:15:11,653 --> 02:15:13,417
Look at that!

1590
02:15:15,170 --> 02:15:16,767
Well done, Leo.

1591
02:15:16,768 --> 02:15:17,768
You too, John.

1592
02:15:37,084 --> 02:15:40,415
<i>Explain to me how he's finished first
if he's not won the race?</i>

1593
02:15:40,415 --> 02:15:44,534
<i>Because McLaren started from further,
so he came into and he won.</i>

1594
02:15:44,534 --> 02:15:46,035
It's not a tie!

1595
02:15:46,361 --> 02:15:48,684
Because McLaren started further
back, they're saying.

1596
02:15:48,685 --> 02:15:51,409
He's traveled a little bit further.
So, he's won and not Ken.

1597
02:15:51,410 --> 02:15:53,188
That's bullshit!

1598
02:15:53,328 --> 02:15:55,306
Shel, hold on!

1599
02:16:09,349 --> 02:16:12,149
Where is the tie?
Where is the goddamn tie?

1600
02:16:12,273 --> 02:16:13,273
What?

1601
02:16:13,494 --> 02:16:14,494
You son of a bitch!

1602
02:16:15,006 --> 02:16:16,357
- You knew!
- I didn't, I swear.

1603
02:16:16,358 --> 02:16:17,856
Enough!

1604
02:16:20,374 --> 02:16:22,627
Nice race, mate. Congrats.

1605
02:16:44,356 --> 02:16:46,048
Shel!

1606
02:16:49,992 --> 02:16:51,690
They robbed you, Ken.

1607
02:16:51,691 --> 02:16:56,153
<i>Here's the clarification, though the
drivers finished the race in a heat,</i>

1608
02:16:56,153 --> 02:16:59,624
<i>McLaren has been ruled the winner
as he started from farther back.</i>

1609
02:16:59,625 --> 02:17:02,153
Some bullshit technicality.

1610
02:17:15,321 --> 02:17:17,362
I never should've asked you.

1611
02:17:22,981 --> 02:17:25,132
Selling cars, huh?

1612
02:17:27,412 --> 02:17:29,168
That's what they do.

1613
02:17:29,757 --> 02:17:30,655
Well,

1614
02:17:31,221 --> 02:17:33,694
you promised me the drive,

1615
02:17:35,833 --> 02:17:37,797
not the win.

1616
02:17:38,297 --> 02:17:40,396
It was a hell of a drive.

1617
02:17:40,922 --> 02:17:42,850
She's a hell of a machine.

1618
02:17:43,308 --> 02:17:45,002
She's fast.

1619
02:17:46,437 --> 02:17:48,209
Could be faster.

1620
02:17:49,754 --> 02:17:51,810
The 7 liter's sweet.

1621
02:17:54,087 --> 02:17:59,592
We still need a lighter chassis.
I was thinking bonded aluminum.

1622
02:17:59,688 --> 02:18:05,546
It's a ground up rebuild, but if it works
we can lose a couple of hundred pounds.

1623
02:18:05,694 --> 02:18:07,712
What the hell are we doing here?

1624
02:18:09,036 --> 02:18:11,436
Let me take a shower,
get a cup of tea.

1625
02:18:11,585 --> 02:18:13,343
Ham and cheese cob or something.

1626
02:18:13,965 --> 02:18:16,363
We gonna get the bastards next year.

1627
02:18:40,068 --> 02:18:42,628
Got a bit of fuel left in the tank.

1628
02:18:43,581 --> 02:18:47,542
What do you think of those honeycomb
panels. What you were looking for?

1629
02:18:47,543 --> 02:18:49,920
I don't know yet.

1630
02:19:14,294 --> 02:19:16,734
She looks pretty good.

1631
02:19:26,375 --> 02:19:30,131
<i>There's a point at 7000 RPM</i>

1632
02:19:31,252 --> 02:19:33,867
<i>where everything fades.</i>

1633
02:19:35,858 --> 02:19:40,932
<i>The machine becomes
weightless, Just disappears.</i>

1634
02:19:42,350 --> 02:19:47,425
<i>And all that's left is a body
moving through space and time.</i>

1635
02:19:50,182 --> 02:19:55,410
<i>7000 RPM, that's where you need it.</i>

1636
02:19:56,818 --> 02:20:01,586
<i>You feel it coming.
It creeps up on you, close in your ear,</i>

1637
02:20:09,107 --> 02:20:13,926
<i>and asks you a question.
The only question that matters.</i>

1638
02:20:19,394 --> 02:20:20,662
<i>Get the van!</i>

1639
02:20:21,984 --> 02:20:24,143
<i>"Who are you?"</i>

1640
02:20:57,191 --> 02:20:58,281
What do you think?

1641
02:20:58,282 --> 02:21:02,918
It's fantastic! That was really good.
Nice and smooth.

1642
02:21:03,886 --> 02:21:06,145
No vibration in the box.
It was really strong.

1643
02:21:06,146 --> 02:21:10,711
You drove her for less than an hour,
you can't tell shit after an hour.

1644
02:21:14,003 --> 02:21:15,936
Hey, Shel.

1645
02:21:25,303 --> 02:21:30,956
Hey, Shell. That guy, the one in the hat.
He's ready to close on those two 427's.

1646
02:21:30,956 --> 02:21:36,977
His and hers, full freight.
They flew in from Galveston.

1647
02:21:40,759 --> 02:21:43,883
I need you to come outside
for maybe a minute.

1648
02:21:44,339 --> 02:21:46,148
And do what?

1649
02:21:47,442 --> 02:21:49,453
Be Carroll Shelby.

1650
02:21:49,963 --> 02:21:52,823
Tell them a story.
Spin a few magic words.

1651
02:21:53,215 --> 02:21:56,233
What does that mean?
Magic words?

1652
02:21:57,209 --> 02:22:00,896
It means, come
outside, and say hello,

1653
02:22:00,897 --> 02:22:02,921
and make them feel good
about their purchase.

1654
02:22:02,930 --> 02:22:06,406
They're getting the damn cars.
That's what they get for their money, Phil.

1655
02:22:06,532 --> 02:22:09,336
Either they want them or they don't.
Am I some kind of a lounge act?!

1656
02:22:09,336 --> 02:22:12,286
- No.
- Am I here to talk people into things?!

1657
02:22:23,092 --> 02:22:25,590
It's been 6 months, Shel.

1658
02:22:26,407 --> 02:22:28,489
Six months.

1659
02:22:32,472 --> 02:22:35,319
Sometimes, they don't get
out of the car.

1660
02:23:10,146 --> 02:23:11,993
Peter!

1661
02:23:12,446 --> 02:23:15,028
Peter, come and take
the garbage out!

1662
02:23:15,029 --> 02:23:17,193
<i>Mr. Shelby?</i>

1663
02:23:18,193 --> 02:23:19,761
Hello, Pete.

1664
02:23:21,434 --> 02:23:23,490
I remember that wrench.

1665
02:23:24,222 --> 02:23:26,043
My Dad threw it at you.

1666
02:23:27,312 --> 02:23:29,077
I believe he did.

1667
02:23:29,512 --> 02:23:30,803
Why?

1668
02:23:33,286 --> 02:23:34,387
Oh.

1669
02:23:35,646 --> 02:23:38,116
I think I probably
said something to him.

1670
02:23:38,755 --> 02:23:40,538
Called him a few names.

1671
02:23:42,300 --> 02:23:44,114
That's right.

1672
02:23:52,582 --> 02:23:54,757
Do you wanna speak to my Mum?

1673
02:23:54,882 --> 02:24:00,158
Well, I did. I came to say hello,
check in on her and

1674
02:24:04,640 --> 02:24:07,438
then, I started thinking sometimes

1675
02:24:09,235 --> 02:24:16,157
that words just are not useful.

1676
02:24:21,866 --> 02:24:24,445
Tools are useful 'cause you
can make stuff with 'em,

1677
02:24:24,446 --> 02:24:26,470
and you can fix stuff with 'em.

1678
02:24:27,491 --> 02:24:28,984
Here.

1679
02:24:29,920 --> 02:24:31,581
Thanks.

1680
02:24:39,714 --> 02:24:42,218
Your Daddy was a...

1681
02:24:44,875 --> 02:24:47,334
He was your friend.

1682
02:24:52,752 --> 02:24:54,676
Yes, he was.

1683
02:24:55,440 --> 02:24:57,182
Yes, sir.

1684
02:25:01,971 --> 02:25:05,406
And he thought you was
just finer than frog fur.

1685
02:25:09,293 --> 02:25:11,009
<i>Peter!</i>

1686
02:25:16,078 --> 02:25:18,546
I think I've gotta go help my Mum.

1687
02:25:20,281 --> 02:25:23,247
What are you doing
here then? Go on.

